paign stop) add amusing or telling detail to the mosaic of this complex and creative man. Others illustrate the personal approaches or techniques he relied on to persuade, cajole, or otherwise get his way in the rough-and-tumble world of gubernatorial and presidential politics. And all of them add to our understanding of one of New York's most lively and influential governors.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aGeneral Interest : Memoir. 4aNew York/Regional : New York State Government. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aHolcom, Charles R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolcomb, Charles R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844185640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438441856423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438441856/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles